quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to make each word capitalized in the paragraph:
[!raw!]
p.capfirst {
   {0}: {1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The text-transform Property[/h1]

The text-transform CSS property specifies how to capitalize an element's text. For example, it can be used to make text appear with each word capitalized.

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="capitalize">
    The value capitalize transforms the first 
    character in each word to uppercase; 
    all other characters remain unaffected.
</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="529"]p.capitalize {
   text-transform: capitalize;
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2605" width="100%"]

[h1]text-transform Values[/h1]

Using text-transform property you can make text appear in all-uppercase or all-lowercase. Here is an example:

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="uppercase">This value transforms all characters to uppercase.</p>
<p class="lowercase">This value transforms all characters to lowercase.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="530"]p.uppercase {
   text-transform: [b]uppercase;[/b]
}
p.lowercase {
   text-transform:[b] lowercase;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2606" width="100%"]
[note]The value [b]none[/b] will produce no capitalization effect at all. [/note]
